attributes.title: Nike Free Plus 2
attributes.description:
NIKE FREE PLUS 2 CITY PACK - VISUAL CENTER
CREATING THE BRAND STORY AND MESSAGING FOR NIKE FREE.
INFO
For the visual center for Nike Free, we were tasked to do the following: frame the campaign in a narrative, create product photography, produce a zine. Ultimately the challenge led us down many paths and produced numerous results.

For the zine, we decided to shoot four editorials. Three were chosen because of their importance to the campaing, London, NYC and Tokyo. We also choose to do a editorial on the university that inspired the Nike Free with Oliver Helbig, a regular contributer to 032C magazine. With four photo shoots in hour days, the DualForces team had their hands full and soon we trying to find which of the amazing images to use for the zine.

The 56 page zine was nearly all distressed with a heavy half tone pattern that conveyed the democratic and low fidelity technology that also drives the Nike Free shoe. We printed 16 pages in glossy color to highlight Oliver's editorial and call out the beauty in humanless photography.

Early on we photographed all of the shoes and delivered print ready files to Nike's BNX servers. We also created several hero images to be used in packaging, shirts and on the boxes.

attributes.title: Undertrained StyleGAN
attributes.description:
Generative adversarial networks (GANs) have become a popular technique in recent years for generating artificial images that mimic real photos. One popular GAN architecture is StyleGAN, developed by researchers at NVIDIA. StyleGAN allows high-resolution image generation with intricate details and lifelike results. However, training these models requires massive datasets of images in order for the GAN to accurately capture the distribution of real photos.

This art project explores what happens when StyleGAN models are deliberately undertrained on smaller datasets. The lack of sufficient training data causes the models to produce images filled with visual glitches and distortions. The ghostly, fragmented results have an eerie, surreal quality. While the images are no longer realistic, the aesthetic artifacts from the incomplete training process create striking visual compositions. This project toys with machine learning algorithms, subverting them to produce digital artworks that reflect on artificial intelligence and its limitations. The strange imagery hints at the tensions between the natural flaws of current AI systems and their aspirations toward mimicking human creativity.
